EXTRACTED VALUE: Eve flashed on a dingy room, the bloody husk of a man, and the child she'd been, huddled broken in a corner. "I don't have any family."
She nodded. "On Wales and on England, and on Spain itself."
"Of course, of course. I don't wish to delay you..."
"In his view, I should have been on top of the situation sooner."
"No, I didn't," Nell said. "He was the right guy for twenty-two years." She stared into her coffee cup. "It's not like he cheated"
"How about homeless shelters? Places we sleep when it's ten degrees outside. How many shelters are listed there in those papers?"
"You have to give these to the police," I said.
